From: art-suite conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] cet_cmake_env(NO_INSTALL_PKGMETA): do not auto-install LICENSE/README

cetmodules' cet_cmake_env() calls install_pkgmeta(), which installs the project's
top-level LICENSE/README as files at $PREFIX root. ROOT (a host dep here) owns
$PREFIX/README as a *directory*; installing our README file over it chmods that
directory to 0644 and rattler-build's post-build step then aborts (EPERM). Same
fatal clash canvas_root_io hit. NO_INSTALL_PKGMETA suppresses the automatic
install_pkgmeta() call (the cetmodules-native fix). Generated against the tree
with 0001 already applied. See potential_improvements.md (#7).

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -4,7 +4,7 @@ find_package(cetmodules 2.13.00 REQUIRED)
 project(art_root_io VERSION 1.14.01 LANGUAGES CXX C)

 include(CetCMakeEnv)
-cet_cmake_env()
+cet_cmake_env(NO_INSTALL_PKGMETA)

 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS VIGILANT DWARF_VER 4
   NO_UNDEFINED
